<br>
How do I feel about it as a skald?  Well...more depressed than I had before.  Most of us have always argued not that our class is bad, but that the changes to other classes have steadily marginalized our abilities (the so-called &quot;passive nerf&quot;).<br>
<br>
1.62 continues this trend as far as I can see.  Other classes that have under-performed will get some improvements, which once again downgrades our place in the endgame food chain.  <br>
<br>
- Increases to the melee damage of other classes makes skald damage less valuable to benefit a group.<br>
- Increases to the support abilities of other classes highlights the lesser effect of our own.<br>
<br>
Most importantly:<br>
<br>
- Improvements to the defensive ability of all melee classes highlights how low our defence is, while reducing once again our overall damage (i.e. we will not really parry much more than we did, but more of our own blows will fail to reach their target).  This last one is the largest downward effect I can see i this patch.<br>
<br>
Maybe it's the constant bumping of our dev board skald thread with seemingly no effect, but I'm as burned out by the downward spiral of our class as many others were months ago.  Guess it took me longer to catch up to the skald malaise, but I got here finally. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whorde>whorde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/22/03 5:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=609.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Most importantly:<br>
