=======================<br>
Our snare is no longer unique; and triggers the immunity timer whereas melee snares do not. Players can now get the same ability, albeit a better version of it, by chosing a class other than a skald. Additionally, our damage add will break melee snares; which could be considered one more reason NOT to use it. There are becoming fewer and fewer reasons to play a skald instead of another class.<br>
=======================<br>
Agreed (surprise su-frick'n-prise)<br>
<br>
Skalds offer CC:<br>
<br>
Snare: See above.<br>
<br>
Mezz: less than 15s on tanks, maximum 29ish seconds.  1 minute immunity, even less duration total on sorc groups, same immunity as primary CC healer class.<br>
<br>
All of that makes our CC a gimick, and no longer a way to offset our lack of defense/group support, and standard hybrid offense.  It use to be that one advantage we had was vs 2 opponents, we could mezz one, fight the other.  Now, we really do not have the option, and snare is now basically just a ranged interrupt.<br>
